== FAQ ==

Why does my environment rebuild gcc-cross, binutils-cross, and libtool-cross 

If every end-user had the same username and the same OE_HOME, then the cross-toolchain would be completely portable. However, that is generally not the case. The toolchain has compiled-in paths that contain system libraries and headers. If those paths change, then there is a very high probability that [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gremlin gremlins] might attack you, your loved ones, and your town, possibly ruining Christmas for everyone.

